108. massa] This word, from μα’ζα a lump of dough, implies something of which the component parts are so thoroughly amalgainated that separation is no longer possible. It is· often used of hot iron (μύδρος), and Virgil> has ‘ atrae massam picis,’ Georg. i. 275. It is well applied to the chaotic mass while its parts, though separable, were intimately blended.
